Git & GitHub Complete Revision Notes

What is Git?
- Git is a Version Control System (VCS).
- It helps track changes in source code.
- Every developer has their own Local Repository on their machine.
- Git allows multiple developers to work on the same project efficiently.

What is GitHub?
- GitHub is a cloud-based platform that hosts Git repositories.
- It acts as a Remote Repository.
- It is used for code storage, collaboration, code review, and project management.

--------------------------------------------------

Git Workflow

Working Directory
↓
Staging Area
↓
Local Repository
↓
Remote Repository (GitHub)

Working Directory
- Contains project files on your local machine.
- Any modifications are made here first.

Staging Area
- Temporary area where files are prepared before committing.
- Files are moved here using the git add command.

Local Repository
- Stores committed changes on your local machine.
- Commits act as checkpoints or snapshots of your code.

Remote Repository
- Repository hosted on GitHub.
- Used for sharing code and collaboration.

--------------------------------------------------

Git Installation & Initial Setup

Check Git Installation

git --version

Create a New Local Repository

git init

Note:
- Creates a new Git repository.
- Run only once per project.

Configure Username

git config --global user.name "Sameer"

Configure Email

git config --global user.email "sameeridea7@gmail.com"

Verify Configuration

git config --list

or

git config --global user.name
git config --global user.email

--------------------------------------------------

Adding Files to Staging Area

Add All Files

git add -A

Add a Specific File

git add filename

Example:
git add LoginPage.java

Add All Java Files

git add *.java

Add an Entire Folder

git add foldername

Purpose:
- Moves files from Working Directory to Staging Area.

--------------------------------------------------

Commit Changes

git commit -m "Message"

Example:

git commit -m "Added Login Feature"

Purpose:
- Saves staged changes into the Local Repository.

Flow:
Staging Area → Local Repository

--------------------------------------------------

Push Changes to GitHub

git push origin main

or

git push origin master

Purpose:
- Uploads committed changes from Local Repository to GitHub.

Flow:
Local Repository → Remote Repository

--------------------------------------------------

Pull Latest Changes from GitHub

git pull

Purpose:
- Downloads latest changes from GitHub to your local machine.

Flow:
Remote Repository → Local Repository

--------------------------------------------------

Clone an Existing Repository

git clone https://github.com/pavanoltraining/OpencartV121.git

Purpose:
- Copies a GitHub repository to your local machine.

--------------------------------------------------

Git Status

git status

Purpose:
- Shows current repository status.
- Displays modified files.
- Displays staged files.
- Displays untracked files.

--------------------------------------------------

View Commit History

Detailed History

git log

Short History

git log --oneline

Purpose:
- Shows commit history.
- Displays Commit ID, Author, Date, and Message.

